data.chText: 想出（主意、计划等）；想象；构想；设想
data.enText: to form an idea, a plan, etc. in your mind; to imagine sth

data.chText: 他想出了一个把旧发电站改造为艺术中心的主意。
data.enText: He conceived the idea of transforming the old power station into an arts centre.

data.chText: 上帝常常被想象为男性。
data.enText: God is often conceived of as male.

data.chText: 我无法想象他会存心伤害我们。
data.enText: I cannot conceive (= I do not believe) (that) he would wish to harm us.

data.chText: 我想象不出它会是什么样子。
data.enText: I cannot conceive what it must be like.
when a woman conceives or conceives a child , she becomes pregnant

data.chText: 他们的第一个小孩是在新婚之夜怀上的。
data.enText: Their first child was conceived on their wedding night.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 共同 + ceive 抓 → 大家一起抓〔思想〕→ 想像；构想

ex.chText: 这座桥是斯科特设计的。
ex.enText: This bridge was designed by Scott.

ex.chText: 为了赢得比赛，她设计了一套华丽的婚纱礼服。
ex.enText: She designed a gorgeous wedding dress in order to win the competition.

ex.chText: 他得到了一份网站设计工作。
ex.enText: He has a job desiging websites.

ex.chText: 这些项目是为了发展经济而设计的。
ex.enText: These programs are designed to develop the economy.

ex.chText: 这项培训是为老师设计的。
ex.enText: This training is designed for teachers.

synonyms.bx: 主要指设计建筑、衣物、软件等，强调构思多于实际制造；也可指为了某种特定目的而设计，通常用被动语态。

ex.chText: 那位科学家有了新武器的设想。
ex.enText: The scientist conceived of the idea of a new weapon.

ex.chText: 他构想出了第一台真正的便携式计算机。
ex.enText: He conceived of the idea to make the first truly portable computer.

synonyms.bx: 通常指想出新的主意、计划等，强调在制订计划之前先有的构思。

ex.chText: 她对几块印花棉布加以充分利用，设计出了一条裙子。
ex.enText: She made full use of several pieces of calico and contrived a skirt from them.

ex.chText: 你能用这些垂下来的藤条做个秋千吗？
ex.enText: Can you contrive a swing from the hanging vines?

synonyms.bx: 尤指因突然需要而巧妙地造出或设计出某物。

example: My daughter was conceived in Christmas Day
I think he is very smart
I believe her to be very smart
I think that he is her boyfriend
The racist conceives such people to be inferior
He conceived of a robot that would help paralyzed patients

value.def: If you cannot conceive of something, you cannot imagine it or believe it.

example.ex: I just can't even conceive of that quantity of money...
example.tran: 那么多钱，我根本都无法想象。

example.ex: He was immensely ambitious but unable to conceive of winning power for himself.
example.tran: 他雄心勃勃，但是想不出自己能如何赢得权力。

value.def: If you conceive something as a particular thing, you consider it to be that thing.

example.ex: The ancients conceived the earth as afloat in water...
example.tran: 古人认为地球飘浮在水里。

example.ex: We conceive of the family as being in a constant state of change...
example.tran: 我们认为家庭处于不断变化之中。

example.ex: Elvis conceived of himself as a ballad singer.
example.tran: 埃尔维斯认为自己是民谣歌手。

value.def: If you conceive a plan or idea, you think of it and work out how it can be done.

example.ex: She had conceived the idea of a series of novels...
example.tran: 她萌生出撰写系列小说的想法。

example.ex: He conceived of the first truly portable computer in 1968.
example.tran: 1968年，他构想出第一台真正的便携式计算机。

value.def: When a woman conceives, she becomes pregnant.

example.ex: Women, he says, should give up alcohol before they plan to conceive...
example.tran: 他说女性在计划怀孕之前应该戒酒。

example.ex: About one in six couples has difficulty conceiving...
example.tran: 大约1/6的夫妻有受孕困难。

example.ex: A mother who already has non-identical twins is more likely to conceive another set of twins.
example.tran: 生育过非同卵双胞胎的母亲再怀上双胞胎的可能性更大。
